The 255 character limit on swimlane and filter jql is annoying and takes away the power of GreenHopper.

*Workaround*

Save the filter separately in the Issue Navigator and then reference the filter (with all those chars) in the Swimlane/QuickFilter config with savedFilter = XYZ

The rapid board filter configuration currently forces your {{JQL}} query to explicitly "{{ORDER BY Rank}}" to enable ranking.

We have encapsulated our rapid board filters in JQL function plugins to make them easier to use and maintain. E.g.:

{{issue in myRapidBoardFunction(PROJ)}}

Our functions are ordering by rank but the rapid board filter configuration still forces us to add ordering explicitly to enable ranking:

{{issue in myRapidBoardFunction(PROJ) ORDER BY Rank ASC}}

I would like to suggest adding an override option to the default behaviour to get around the unnecessary additional ordering in these cases.

